<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Albanese arrives in China for landmark visit, says it’s in ‘our national interest’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/05/anthony-albanese-arrives-for-china-visit-meeting-xi-jinping-and-li-qiang-in-australia-national-interest]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T21:26:24Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7fe1eba235dbaa3dbd98bf871575e45e7b89144d/0_479_8058_4835 /master/8058.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=f0ed77d44fbcd01141bfe2da56cbfaee&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Anthony Albanese 于周六晚抵达中国上海虹桥机场。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/australia-news/anthony-albanese&quot;>;安东尼·阿尔巴内塞&lt;/a>;宣布澳大利亚将“尽我们所能与中国合作，在总理抵达中华人民共和国进行具有里程碑意义的为期三天的正式访问时，我们必须不同意，但……也要参与我们的国家利益。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿尔巴内塞于周六晚上抵达上海。在机场受到两国高级外交官的接见后，总理立即前往上海出席中国总理李强为中国国际进口博览会开幕举行的宴会。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;从宴会回来后总理告诉旅行记者，与我们最大的贸易伙伴中国进行积极、建设性、尊重和开放的对话符合澳大利亚的国家利益。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/commentisfree/2023/nov/04/anthony-albanese-china-trip-xi-jinping-meeting-australia-relationship&quot;>;安东尼·阿尔巴内斯会见习近平是中国和澳大利亚之间重建信任的一步——但它能持续下去吗？&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“这就是我希望在未来几天实现的目标，”总理说。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿尔巴尼斯在国内面临一些批评，因为在澳大利亚人面临生活成本压力之际，他仍保持繁忙的国际旅行计划。总理周六晚上指出，中国是澳大利亚最大的贸易伙伴，阿尔巴内斯指出澳大利亚四分之一的工作岗位“依赖于贸易”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿尔巴内斯对中国的访问是自 2016 年以来澳大利亚总理的首次访问.他将于周一在北京会见中国国家主席习近平，周二会见总理。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www .theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/04/a-new-chapter-how-china-sees-albaneses-ice-broken-state-visit&quot;>;新篇章：中国如何看待阿尔巴尼斯的“破冰行动” &#39; 国事访问&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;此次访问的目的是在澳大利亚决定将中国公司华为排除在 5G 网络建设之外之后一段时期的重大动荡之后重启外交关系2018年。时任总理斯科特·莫里森呼吁对2020年大流行的起源进行独立调查后，双边裂痕加剧并演变成贸易战。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周日，总理将出席贸易战参观上海世博会，并在澳大利亚旅游局组织的活动中会见澳大利亚和中国商界领袖，然后晚上飞往北京。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Albanese 表示，他打算在这次访问期间提出人权和领事问题。周六，在离开澳大利亚之前，阿尔巴内斯被问到他会对中国总理兼国家主席杨恒均说些什么，杨恒均一直在&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023 /nov/01/yang-hengjuns-australian-writer-jailed-china-family-plea-albanese-negotiate-release&quot;>;被拘留四年。&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/commentisfree/2023/nov/04/can-anthony-albanese-catch-the-dragons-tail-to-defrost -and-reboot-australia-china-relations&quot;>;安东尼·艾博尼斯能否抓住龙尾，解冻并重启澳中关系？ |凯瑟琳·墨菲&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;阿尔巴尼斯说：“我会说杨博士的案子需要解决。我将谈论他的人权、拘留的性质以及透明程序的失败。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“当我们与国际领导人会面时，我们将始终提出澳大利亚公民的问题。这是我们一贯做的事情，我会以一种旨在为杨博士及其家人的利益取得成果的方式再次这样做。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 05:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Zelenskiy denies he is under pressure to enter peace talks with Russia]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/zelenskiy-denies-he-is-under-pressure-to-enter-peace-talks-with-russia]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T16:03:15Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/41b4b721c348d19be1ede54ed48f3c868a100b79/97_194_2790_1673 /master/2790.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=eb1028852c0d8c03a35892a80d1cd9c5&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;欧盟委员会主席乌苏拉·冯德莱恩 (Ursula von der Leyen) 与弗拉基米尔·泽伦斯基 (Volodymyr Zelenskiy) 一起抵达乌克兰基辅举行的新闻发布会。周六。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;乌克兰总统弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基 (Volodymyr Zelenskiy) 否认了西方国家向基辅施压，要求其与俄罗斯进行和平谈判的说法。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;此前，美国全国广播公司 (NBC) 报道了美国和欧洲官员的报道。已与乌克兰政府讨论了与俄罗斯可能进行的和平谈判可能需要采取什么措施来结束战争。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六，泽连斯基否认乌克兰与俄罗斯的战争已经陷入“僵局”，反驳了西方领导人的​​说法。游说和平谈判。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“时间已经过去，人们已经疲倦了……但这并不是僵局，”泽伦斯基在基辅与欧盟委员会主席乌苏拉·冯德莱恩一起举行的新闻发布会上表示。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;“我们的合作伙伴中没有人向我们施压，要求我们与俄罗斯坐下来交谈，并给它一些东西。”&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/nov/04/continued-support-for-ukraine-will-cost-the-west-less-than-letting-putin-win&quot;>;继续支持乌克兰将比让普京获胜让西方付出更少的代价菲利普·英曼&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;本周，乌克兰总司令瓦莱里·扎卢日尼 (Valerii Zaluzhnyi) 告诉《经济学人》：“就像第一次世界大战一样，我们已经达到了使我们陷入了僵局。很可能不会有深刻而漂亮的突破。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但泽连斯基表示，2022年，人们普遍认为乌克兰军队在取得进展之前处于胶着状态。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;“一些军事伎俩，你记得，哈尔科夫地区就解放了。我们没有权利放弃。还有什么选择呢？什么，我们需要放弃三分之一的州？这只是一个开始。我们知道什么是冻结冲突，我们已经为自己得出了结论。我们需要与防空伙伴进行更多合作，疏通天空，让我们的战斗机有机会进行进攻行动。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;随着战争进入第 20 个月，乌克兰 &lt;a href=&quot;https: //www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/08/as-ukraine-reels-from-attacks-on-land-conflict-at-sea-signals-hope&quot;>;努力取得进展&lt;/a>;泽伦斯基表示，以色列和哈马斯之间的战争也转移了人们对乌克兰的注意力，并表示这是“俄罗斯的目标” ”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“当然，很明显，中东战争，这场冲突，正在分散人们的注意力，”泽伦斯基说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们已经陷入了非常严重的境地。” “在几乎没有关注乌克兰的情况下，我们面临着困难的局面，”他说，但他补充道：“我绝对相信我们会克服这一挑战。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乌克兰的支持者，包括美国，坚称他们已准备好为基辅提供军事和财政支持，只要打败俄罗斯就够了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;泽连斯基发表此番言论之际，冯德莱恩访问基辅，讨论乌克兰加入 27 个成员国集团的进展。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;基辅在去年俄罗斯入侵几个月后获得了欧盟候选资格，但分析人士警告说，它面临着一条漫长而艰难的入盟之路。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“你们已经达到了许多里程碑，”冯德莱恩告诉泽连斯基。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“改革司法系统。遏制寡头的控制。打击洗钱等等，”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们永远不应该忘记，你们正在打一场关乎生死存亡的战争，同时你们正在深刻改革你们的国家，”她补充道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >; &lt;p>;她表示，当这些改革实施后，她“相信”乌克兰将在入盟进程中取得进展。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧盟委员会提议在 2027 年之前为乌克兰额外提供 500 亿欧元（合 540 亿美元）资金”，冯德莱恩说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;几乎所有欧盟成员国都支持对基辅提供进一步的长期援助，只有匈牙利和斯洛伐克坚持不懈。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;委员会现在必须在周三之前提交报告一份关于乌克兰以及其他有望加入欧盟的国家摩尔多瓦和格鲁吉亚在 12 月欧盟峰会之前取得多少进展的报告。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 00:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Storm Ciarán leaves seven dead in Italy as torrential rain causes flooding]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/storm-ciaran-italy-deaths-torrential-rain-flooding]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T14:44:01Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c321423c5772ffd8b6a51f8ee76fe1fa9cc3786c/0_87_3072_1844 /master/3072.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=1b0967e359437da9c39f6a81bf65038c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;佛罗伦萨比森齐奥风暴过后，人们在被洪水淹没的街道上&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;第七个人据安莎通讯社报道，意大利中部托斯卡纳地区暴雨导致河流决堤，一天多后，有人被发现死亡，另一人仍然失踪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一具 69 岁老人的尸体该通讯社称，该男子在佛罗伦萨西北约 9 英里（15 公里）的比森齐奥镇被发现。官员早些时候表示，周四晚间开始的洪水已造成六人死亡。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;附近城镇被风暴塞伦南部边缘淹没后，人们担心阿诺河可能会淹没佛罗伦萨，但最高水位周五上午，供水点通过，这座历史名城没有发生重大事件。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/03/tuscany-floods -storm-ciaran-river-flooding&quot;>;塞兰受到从大西洋席卷而来的强大急流的推动&lt;/a>;，带来暴雨和狂风，导致英国、比利时、荷兰和英国部分地区发生严重洪水。法国。安莎社周六援引托斯卡纳地区总统尤金尼奥·贾尼的话说，大约 300 人被迫撤离托斯卡纳的家园，而其他许多人的水和电力供应也被切断。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他补充说，根据初步估计，这场灾难已造成 3 亿欧元（2.6 亿英镑）的损失。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;另一名消防员在威尼托地区东北部失踪， Sky TG24 周五援引了州长的话说。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-atom-id=&quot;4f20a349-36e4-4091-a134-ce3af7b73ceb&quot; data-atom-type=&quot;media&quot;>; &lt;div>; &lt; div style=&quot;font-size:0&quot;>; __YOUTUBE_MEDIA_PLACEHOLDER_4f20a349-36e4-4091-a134-ce3af7b73ceb__ &lt;iframe id=&quot;gu-video-youtube-4f20a349-36e4-4091-a134-ce3af7b73ceb&quot; src=&quot;https://www. youtube-nocookie.com/embed/ay2fchIDjYM?modestbranding=1&amp;amp;showinfo=0&amp;amp;rel=0&amp;amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;amp;embed_config=%7B%22disableAds%22%3Atrue%2C%22nonPersonalizedAd%22%3Atrue%2C%22restrictedDataProcessor%22 %3Atrue%2C%22adsConfig%22%3A%7B%22adTagParameters%22%3A%7B%22cmpGdpr%22%3A1%7D%7D%7D&quot;frameborder=&quot;0&quot;allowfullscreen>;&lt;/iframe>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/ div>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;意大利政府于周五宣布进入紧急状态，并拨款 500 万欧元来帮助受灾最严重的地区。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;意大利多个地区的天气警报仍然有效，在该国遭受强风和大雨袭击一周后，一些学校关闭。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;意大利被认为特别容易受到气候变化的影响。 5 月份艾米利亚-罗马涅地区的洪水导致至少 14 人死亡。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 23:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Toddler in hospital after dumped gun discharges at Las Vegas playground]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/toddler-in-hospital-after-dumped-gun-discharges-at-las-vegas-playground]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T12:53:45Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/6e6128244574395e34271616bd87f89f1ecf9457/0_238_7128_4277 /master/7128.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=f57d47e8700d0151b9307580f29249d7&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;据称，一名青少年在城市公交车上开枪打死一名男子后与他人发生争执。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;当局于周五宣布，拉斯维加斯一名幼儿在日托操场上发现一把枪，该枪是一名向城市公交车开火后逃跑的青少年丢弃的，目前情况危急。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;副警察警长雷吉·雷德 (Reggie Rader) 表示，这名 5 岁以下的幼儿“发现了枪支，捡起了枪，然后枪就开火了。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;雷德表示，这名幼儿目前情况稳定，但情况危急。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;雷德表示，这名幼儿目前情况稳定，但情况危急。警方在拉斯维加斯东北部的日托中心地区发现了嫌疑人并将其拘留。 Rader 没有透露嫌疑人的身份，他说嫌疑人还不到 18 岁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Rader 表示，目前还不清楚这名少年将面临什么指控，但警察局正在与当地地方检察官办公室协商有关事宜。 “所有适用的费用”以及他是否会像成年人一样被收费。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当局称，这名少年当时正在从城市公交车上跑下来，然后跳过一堵墙，进入日托中心的游乐场区域。&lt;/p>; >; &lt;p>;雷德说，这名少年在公交车上与一名男子发生争执，并掏出枪向他开枪。雷德说，该男子也已入院治疗，目前情况稳定。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 21:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Himmler ordered mass execution of prisoners in Britain’s only Nazi camp, documents reveal]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/himmler-execution-prisoners-britain-nazi-concentration-camp]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T13:00:40Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/d783c19daf47a2d5779d2ce7c​​c3fde320592a026/265_221_5192_3117 /master/5192.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=5c2d67bb38660bee3d4a29e6462e87af&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;奥尔德尼集中营俄罗斯囚犯的坟墓。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;海因里希·希姆莱秘密命令《观察家报》此前未公开的文件透露，英国奥尔德尼岛上的 1,000 名奴隶劳工将被冷血枪杀。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;党卫军领导人的直接书面命令这是第一个已知的指示，表明制定计划的目的是消灭英国领土上唯一的纳粹集中营和劳改营的所有居住者。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;希姆莱是大屠杀的关键设计师，他向指挥官们发出指示如果奥尔德尼岛制造麻烦，“立即”谋杀所有囚犯和劳工。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/ aug/13/the-holocaust-happened-on-british-soil-inquiry-into-nazi-camps-creates-bitter-divide-on-alderney&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;纳粹占领&lt;/a>;，海峡群岛，英国皇家属地，设有四个劳工场所，其中包括一个集中营，其中的居住者被迫建造希特勒所谓的大西洋墙的巨大防御工事。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;来自党卫军总部、日期为 1943 年的其他文件表明奥尔德尼岛的囚犯死亡人数可能远多于官方公布的近 400 人死亡人数。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;政府目前正在尝试&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/ 2023/jul/22/nazi-atrocities-jews-prisoners-war-alderney-channel-island-uk&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;通过计算被监禁的囚犯人数来确定&lt;/a>;奥尔德尼岛大屠杀的确切规模由英国大屠杀特使皮克尔斯勋爵领导的持续审查被谋杀。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尽管公众已经&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gov.uk/guidance/public-submissions-to- support-review-into-the-number-of-prisoners-who-died-on-alderney-during-the-nazi-occupation&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;邀请&lt;/a>;向审查提交证据，对向潜在贡献者发出的“居高临下”指示说服了著名战时历史学家和作家伊恩·塞耶 (Ian Sayer) 将其档案中的党卫军文件交给了&lt;em>;观察家&lt;/em>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id= &quot;d468dc93cffe6ab7fb1a49ee975609972f7aea14&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/d468dc93cffe6ab7fb1a49ee975609972f7aea14/1754_804_5726_3438/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;营地的大门。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;营地门口的牌匾。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Carl Court/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/图>; &lt;p>;这些文件中有一封希姆莱写给奥尔德尼岛党卫军建筑旅指挥官马克西米利安·李斯特的信。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;日期为 1943 年 8 月 19 日，标记为绝密希姆莱在信中写道：“一旦发生袭击，如果囚犯有哪怕是最轻微的迹象表明他们打算制造麻烦，你必须立即采取行动，不拘礼节，射杀罪犯。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;“如果秩序仍未恢复，你们必须立即射杀所有囚犯。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这封信是由信使亲手交给李斯特的，并附有希姆莱的具体命令以确保他谋杀数百名手无寸铁且受虐待的奴隶劳工的指示永远不会被公开。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“他[List]将其阅读三遍以上，然后通过您自己再次发回给我，而无需希姆莱说，他对第三帝国的许多最严重的罪行负有责任。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;教授 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis .com/international/lists/tag/profile/richard-j-evans&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;理查德·埃文斯&lt;/a>;，剑桥大学历史学名誉教授，认为希姆莱的命令可能是由于特雷布林卡囚犯起义，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/feb/20/samuel-willenberg-survivor-of-nazi-death-camp-treblinka-dies-ged -93&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;被占领的波兰境内最致命的&lt;/a>;纳粹灭绝营，发生在党卫军头子写信给李斯特的几天前。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“特雷布林卡于 2 日发生了囚犯起义。 1943 年 8 月，希姆莱可能对此感到担忧。也许也是因为五月份的华沙隔都起义。这种反应对希姆莱来说是相当标准的。”埃文斯说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而，德国历史国际专家埃文斯表示，直到八月下旬，才能完全确定党卫军头目是否被告知特雷布林卡起义。&lt; /p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;74a2987111424ce7f5c8ac1692d682cebf94d368&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/74a2987111424ce7f5c8ac1692d682cebf94d368/0_567_2955_1773/1 000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;海因里希·希姆莱。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;海因里希·希姆莱是大屠杀的建筑师之一。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Bettmann/Bettmann Archive&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt; /figure>; &lt;p>;根据之前未公开的文件，更确定的是希姆莱在英国领土上杀害囚犯的命令试图保密。 1943 年 9 月 15 日的另一封信透露，另一名党卫军军官 - &lt;em>;Obergruppenführer&lt;/em>; Oswald Pohl - 通知希姆莱的副官鲁道夫·勃兰特，所有与奥尔德尼岛杀戮命令有关的文件都已被销毁。&lt;/em>; p>; &lt;p>;“关于这个主题的任何书面材料已经不存在了”，这封信也被标记为绝密。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而希姆莱的信以某种方式幸存下来，并且很可能是从党卫军总部被洗劫一空。战后，于 1983 年 6 月在纽约拍卖会上被 Sayer 收购。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com /uk-news/2023/aug/13/the-holocaust-happened-on-british-soil-inquiry-into-nazi-camps-creates-bitter-divide-on-alderney&quot;>;“大屠杀发生在英国土地上” ：对纳粹集中营的调查在奥尔德尼岛造成了严重分歧&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;这位 78 岁的老人因追踪被盗的纳粹黄金和战犯以及领导权威而闻名核实战时文件，但对将其提供给&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gov.uk/government/news/review-into-the-number-of-prisoners-who-died-on 感到不舒服-alderney-during-the-nazi-occupation&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;政府的审查&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“作为多年来协助各种社团、博物馆、作家和记者的人，通过提供我的第二次世界大战档案中的文件副本和信件，我认为我可以做出贡献。”1988 年的 Sayer &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.andrewlownie.co.uk/authors/ian -sayer&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;追踪&lt;/a>;世界上幸存的最高级别纳粹党卫军将军 Wilhelm Mohnke。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Sayer 认为政府对公众提交意见的指示将阻止想要提供帮助的公众，特别是来自调查的威胁，即未以某种格式提供的文件“将被&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gov.uk/guidance/public-submissions-to-support-review-into-the-number -of-prisoners-who-died-on-alderney-during-the-nazi-占领&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;忽视&lt;/a>;”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;将党卫军文件描述为“具有相当大的历史意义” ” 塞耶补充道：“调查本身是一项有价值的事业，但以这种方式对待寻求帮助的人是不对的。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;教授 &lt;a href=&quot;https://committees.parliament .uk/writingevidence/61020/html/&quot;>;奥斯维辛集中营问题的权威专家、加拿大滑铁卢大学的罗伯特·扬·范·佩尔特&lt;/a>;证实了这些文件的真实性，并得出结论称它们“无疑是真实的”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;佩尔特，伦敦否认大屠杀审判的专家证人&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2017/jan/15/david-irving-youtube-inspiring -holocaust-deniers&quot;>;大卫·欧文&lt;/a>;目前也是皮克尔斯领导的奥尔德尼调查专家小组的成员。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;萨耶尔收集的同一套文件揭示了对被指控的党卫军建筑旅的见解在奥尔德尼岛建立纳粹防御工事，其中有一段赞扬了被奴役劳工的职业道德，称“囚犯的生产力与德国工人的生产力相当”。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 21:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[UK urges Iran to use influence to avert escalation in Israel-Hamas conflict]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/uk-urges-iran-influence-escalation-israel-hamas-conflict-gaza]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T11:43:04Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/861c3fc135b30a9b9ac1e8b5355f490fff420e18/832_94_1461_877 /master/1461.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=14cb482315c75a2a9254042d595dcccc&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;詹姆斯·克莱弗利 (James Cleverly) 走在唐宁街&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;英国外交大臣詹姆斯·克莱弗利 (James Cleverly) 罕见地走在唐宁街与伊朗外长的电话强调了西方的警告，即德黑兰必须利用其对中东其他组织的影响力，以防止加沙冲突升级。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;从双方给出的消息中尚不清楚。是否聪明地阐明了如果伊朗被认为积极煽动一场更广泛的战争，会给伊朗带来什么后果，或者他是否提供了任何情报来表明西方了解伊朗参与的深度。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;伊朗外交部长，侯赛因·阿米尔-阿卜杜拉希安 (Hossein Amir-Abdollahian) 拒绝了克莱维利的信息，重申了长期以来的立场，即伊朗不控制巴勒斯坦领土、黎巴嫩、伊拉克、叙利亚或也门的激进组织，也称为“抵抗轴心”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;伊朗外交部在比英国外交部提供的简短摘要更长的通话宣读中表示，敦促克莱弗利对冲突采取现实的态度，并认识到“抵抗力量”正在与以色列政府的占领作斗争这是犯下相当于种族灭绝的战争罪，而且行为不相称。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/ 2023/nov/04/gaza-ceasefire-talks-ongoing-dispite-israeli-pm-rejecting-pause-says-us&quot;>;美国表示，尽管以色列总理拒绝“暂停”，但加沙停火谈判仍在继续&lt;/a>;&lt;/p >; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;阿米尔-阿卜杜拉希安表示，国际法赋予被占领国家的人民自卫的合法权利。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“他指出，正是在这种情况下，9,000 多名巴勒斯坦平民遭到屠杀伊朗外交部报道称，这是犹太复国主义政权公开宣布的报复和种族灭绝行为，从任何角度来看都是不可接受的。阿维夫对该地区战争升级负有责任。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;黎巴嫩真主党领导人哈桑·纳斯拉拉 (Hassan Nasrallah) 声称 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/ nov/03/hezbollah-leader-threatens-escalation-in-fighting-with-israel&quot;>;在周五的一次演讲&lt;/a>;中，该组织通过美国中间人收到警告，如果真主党加入对以色列的战争，美国将攻击伊朗.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;纳斯鲁拉的讲话表明，全面立即升级的威胁已经消退，但在高度动荡的环境中，缓慢升级的可能性仍然存在。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;对美国的袭击伊拉克的基地可能会增加，但哈马斯最希望看到真主党通过在黎巴嫩南部和以色列之间的边界开辟完整的第二条战线来束缚以色列军队。真主党已经损失了 50 名战士。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一些伊朗官员认为，这对美国和以色列的国际地位造成的长期损害是如此巨大，以至于他们在现阶段不需要试图向军队倾斜平衡。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在电话中，克莱弗利还表示&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/oct/30/british-counter-terror-officers-closely -monitoring-iran-amid-heightened-risk&quot;>;伊朗支持的针对英国民众的威胁&lt;/a>;是不可接受的，必须停止。英国情报部门表示，英国人民的生命受到多达 15 项可信威胁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;伊朗最高领导人阿亚图拉阿里哈梅内伊本周早些时候嘲笑了该国巴斯基志愿者的说法。准军事部队正在伦敦和巴黎组织亲巴勒斯坦示威活动。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 20:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Model says her face was edited with AI to look white: ‘It’s very dehumanizing’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/nov/04/fashion-model-ai-image-tiktok]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T11:00:39Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/f26e77006ce1b4accaab8ef8c7fff76c664663c3/0_0_3000_1800 /master/3000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=ba2a91d40fe0924881737b8fdcbc1259&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;来自 tiktok 的并排图像显示 wu 和经过数字处理的白人女性图像&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;一位美籍台湾模特表示，一位知名时装设计师上传了一张经过数码修改的秀场照片，使她看起来像白人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.tiktok.com/@shereenwu/ video/7295068175526481198&quot;>;TikTok&lt;/a>; 关于上周浏览量达到 180 万次的事件，Shereen Wu 表示，曾与 Beyoncé、Jennifer Lopez 和 Celine Dion 合作过的设计师 Michael Costello 在他在 Instagram 上拍摄了最近一场洛杉矶时装秀。这张照片中吴穿着她走上T台时穿着的紧身黑色舞会礼服，但她的脸已经改变，看起来就像是一名白人女性。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在 Instagram 上发布的一份声明中周四，科斯特洛否认更改了这张照片，并在不到 24 小时后删除了这张照片，并表示这张照片是由未指明来源发送给他的“粉丝艺术”，但他“对分享这张照片承担了责任”。声明中写道：“在我的 Instagram Stories 上转发之前我没有多想，因为我的情绪就像过山车一样，转发了我被标记的所有内容。” （科斯特洛没有回应置评请求。）&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;作为一名没有与经纪公司签约的 21 岁独立模特，吴依靠小工作继续工作。她说，她没有为这场在洛杉矶时装周艺术之心举办的时装秀获得报酬。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;对吴来说，这不是问题，只要能让她露面就行。 “我希望通过曝光获得报酬，”她说。 “但我没有曝光，因为这是一张经过编辑的照片。化妆师、美发师或摄影师也没有砍掉我的头。这就是让我非常恼火的地方。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;吴补充说，她的母亲是第一个发现她的脸被替换的人。 “我最初的反应是，‘谁会像这样砍掉一个人的头？’”吴说。 “我的下一个反应是恐惧，然后是一种忧郁感，因为我妈妈不得不看到她女儿的脸被割伤。”科斯特洛在他现已删除的 Instagram 帖子中说，“鉴于[吴的]视频”，他的同名品牌正在“推进法律诉讼”。他的说法确实与吴的故事中较小的观点相矛盾，例如她是时装秀上另一位模特的替代者。根据他的帖子，他没有制作该节目，也不知道吴没有获得她的时间补偿，直到他看到她的 TikTok。 “在通过她的视频发现她没有得到报酬后，我为谢琳的时间和才华提供了补偿，”科斯特洛写道。 ”支付为 30 多名设计师举办时装秀所需的所有模特费用。他说：“我们这样做都是为了曝光，剥夺任何人的曝光就是剥夺他们的时间和尊严。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://www.tiktok .com/@shereenwu/video/7295068175526481198&quot;>; &lt;iframe height=&quot;700&quot; width=&quot;340&quot; src=&quot;https://www.tiktok.com/embed/v2/7295068175526481198&quot;frameborder=&quot;0&quot;allowfullscreen>;&lt; /iframe>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;虽然修改后的秀场照片的来源尚不清楚，但吴相信有人（她不知道是谁）使用人工智能创造了覆盖她的白色面孔，科斯特洛在他的 Instagram 中呼应了这一理论&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;十年前，模特们抱怨她们的身体被修图到了瘦弱的程度。例如，2009 年 Filippa Hamilton &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/model-in-altered-ralph-lauren-ad-speaks-out-20091015-gy25.html&quot;>;当 Ralph Lauren 品牌改变她的形象，将她的臀部缩小到与头一样大时，她大声疾呼。现在，时尚界面临着如何合乎道德地使用人工智能的问题，这项技术已经被性别歧视-刻板印象/&quot;>;被证明&lt;/a>;将种族主义和性别歧视的刻板印象融入到其创造的图像中。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;今年早些时候，李维斯 (Levi&#39;s) 宣布将在其网站上使用计算机生成的模型来努力包含 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/apr/03/ai-virtual-models-fashion-brands?utm_term=Autofeed&amp;amp;CMP=twt_gu&amp;amp;utm_medium&amp;amp;utm_source=Twitter# Echobox=1680522321&quot;>;不同的种族&lt;/a>;。该决定的批评者表示，如果品牌真正希望丰富有色人种，他们应该聘请人体模特。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;对于福特汉姆时尚法研究所学术主任苏珊·斯卡菲迪 (Susan Scafidi) 来说，用人工智能改变真实模特的种族是另一回事&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Shereen 的修改后的形象凸显了一种可能性，即吸收了主流审美偏好的人工智能程序可能会完全消除模特的种族，从而使时尚行业的进步倒退。跑道上的多样性，”斯卡菲迪说。 She said Wu and other models had little recourse in these situations: copyright law protects photographers whose work is altered without permission, but it does not extend to the models they shoot.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Wu said: “I hope people can understand how hurtful it is to have your work stolen from you. It&#39;s very dehumanizing. The very thing that makes us human is our ability to create something beautiful, and to have this beauty be twisted into something that can potentially be ugly is a terrifying thought.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As Sinead Bovell, a model and tech commentator who &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vogue.com/article/sinead-bovell-model-artificial-intelligence&quot;>;wrote&lt;/a>; about the ethics of AI models for Vogue in 2020, put it: “[Wu] was erased from the digital world, which matters because the digital world is a real place for models. It leads to real economic and visible pathways.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;This is not the first controversy attached to Costello&#39;s name. In 2021, Chrissy Teigen, the model and cookbook author, faced allegations of bullying. As the Cut reported, Costello added to the pile-on, sharing screenshots via Instagram of a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thecut.com/2021/06/the-michael-costello-bullying-controversy-explained.html&quot;>;supposed&lt;/a>; DM conversation with Teigen that left him “traumatized, depressed” with “thoughts of suicide”. But after he posted, others accused Costello of sexual harassment, racism and body shaming, and Teigen said that the screenshots had been altered, statements Costello described as false.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;After Costello&#39;s threat of legal action over her viral Tiktok, Wu contacted the Model Alliance, an advocacy group for fashion workers, which referred her to a lawyer.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“For over a decade, we&#39;ve heard from models who have walked into a store or browsed a company&#39;s website only to find that their image has been heavily manipulated or otherwise used without their informed consent or compensation,” Sara Ziff, founder of the Model Alliance, said. “Unfortunately, Shereen&#39;s experience is one of the many examples of why models need protections as workers.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ultimately, as Ziff said, “AI technology may be new, but the problem of models&#39; images being misused is not.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 19:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russell Brand accused of sexually assaulting extra on US film set]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/nov/04/russell-brand-faces-sexual-assault-lawsuit-in-new-york]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T08:52:13Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/018eef292ebb620443781e90ed60938e90f456f6/0_0_4331_2887/master/4331.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=40b7c085f2aa6aec15b0ef891157fe1c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;British comedian and actor Russell Brand pictured outside London&#39;s Wembley Park Theatre in September, where he was performing.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Russell Brand has been accused in a lawsuit of sexually assaulting a film extra on the New York City set of the 2011 romantic comedy Arthur.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The lawsuit, filed on Friday, was brought in state court under New York&#39;s Adult Survivors Act, which gives accusers a one-year window to sue over alleged non-recent sexual abuse, even if statutes of limitations have expired.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The suit follows a recent flurry of allegations reported in the British media against the 48-year-old actor and comedian by several women accusing him of sexual assault and inappropriate behaviour, during a seven-year period, between 2006 and 2013.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/oct/02/russell-brand-facing-second-criminal-investigation-into-harassment-and-stalking&quot;>;Russell Brand facing second criminal inquiry after harassment allegations&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Brand has denied accusations made by four women in an investigation by the Sunday Times, the Times and Channel 4&#39;s Dispatches and said his relationships were always consensual.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;British police said they were investigating some allegations. No arrests have been made.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Brand&#39;s representatives in New York and London did not immediately respond to requests for comment from the Reuters news agency on the newly filed lawsuit.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Warner Bros Pictures, which distributed the film Arthur, was also named as a defendant, along with other companies involved in the film production. They were accused of negligence and of aiding and abetting Brand by tolerating his misconduct on the set. Warner Bros did not respond to a request for comment from the Reuters news agency.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The complaint was brought by a woman identified only as Jane Doe, who said she was hired to appear as a cast “extra” in a scene.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The film was a remake of a 1981 movie starring Dudley Moore in the title role.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The lawsuit alleges that Brand was visibly intoxicated during the production and exposed his genitalia to the plaintiff as he sat at a table staring at her, “openly and obviously in the presence of everyone on set”, including film studio employees who treated his behaviour as acceptable.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Afterwards, the complaint alleges, Brand followed the woman into a restroom, where he again pulled down his pants, then shoved her into a stall and forced her to perform oral sex on him, while a production crew member stood directly outside as if to guard the door.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The accuser says the assault caused “severe psychological injuries” and economic losses. The suit seeks unspecified money damages from Brand on grounds of assault, battery, false imprisonment and infliction of emotional distress.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Brand, the former husband of the US pop singer Katy Perry and once one of Britain&#39;s most high-profile comedians and broadcasters, has repositioned himself in recent years as an internet social commentator, with more than 6 million followers on his YouTube channel.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;YouTube in September said it had blocked Brand from earning further revenues from the online video platform in light of his alleged sexual misconduct.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 17:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Property porn’ estate agent The Modern House cuts staff amid downturn]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/nov/04/property-estate-agent-the-modern-house-staff-instagram-market]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T08:00:33Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/bbe6b8e18cb8d25c9e573894020b5376f353b397/0_29_1173_704/master/1173.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=7548fc02fb3504a7cbc17bbbf2b6d32c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Modern House property Withdean Road&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Its website specialising in architecturally striking properties has long provided inspiration for well-heeled househunters, and escapism for many more who could never afford to live the dream it is peddling.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Modern House is a go-to site for people who want to browse, or just gawp at, beautiful homes – from spacious apartments in former factories to futuristic Grand Designs-style new-builds. But now, the realities of the UK&#39;s property market slowdown appear to have caught up with the company.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Guardian has been told that The Modern House has cut up to 20%-25% of its staff in an apparent effort to reduce costs after growing rapidly during the pandemic.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Its own website this week listed 44 people working for the company – down from 61 in August. About 20 workers appear to have left since August, and an individual with connections to the business claimed most of these were made redundant during the past few weeks, with the editorial and marketing teams bearing the brunt.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Modern House is one of a number of UK estate agent firms laying off workers or changing hands as rising interest rates and the cost of living crisis squeeze the sector and fuel worries about a possible house price crash.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;2c9ad5e9bf1be99f6a991700185042abb6748d5c&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/2c9ad5e9bf1be99f6a991700185042abb6748d5c/0_107_1600_960/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Warehouse property in Hastings, East Sussex&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;The Modern House is known for its Instagram-friendly homes, such as this warehouse property in Hastings, East Sussex.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: The Modern House&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;However, some of those who regularly visit The Modern House&#39;s beautifully laid-out website or Instagram feed to browse its “collections” – from rural retreats and brutalist homes to warehouse conversions and London mews houses – may not have even realised it is an estate agent, and perhaps assumed it was an upmarket interiors or lifestyle brand. In truth, it is probably both.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Modern House was set up in 2005 by two friends, Albert Hill (formerly the architecture and design editor at Wallpaper* magazine) and Matt Gibberd (a former senior editor at The World of Interiors magazine) after Hill heard about a real estate firm in Florida specialising in mid-century modern houses and wondered whether something similar could work in the UK.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Its name was inspired by FRS Yorke&#39;s 1934 book of the same name, which introduced modernist architecture to a British audience, and its target audience is wealthy young professionals searching for design-led properties “that pay attention to space, light, materials, nature and decoration” and are keen to live in “more thoughtful and beautiful ways”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;However, arguably its biggest audience – or fanbase – is people who, thanks to years of skyrocketing house prices, probably have no chance of being able to afford one of these light-filled loft apartments or sprawling barn conversions, but – to put it bluntly – like scrolling through a bit of “property porn” during an idle moment.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;4ddac06806542f25b7e1e343c38216c99b114001&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/4ddac06806542f25b7e1e343c38216c99b114001/0_480_7667_4603/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Wingfield, Wiltshire&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;This house in Wingfield, Wiltshire, is for sale for £1.25m through The Modern House offshoot Inigo.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Inigo&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;The company has moved far beyond its original roots, with various spin-offs and ventures. In addition to a sister platform for period properties called Inigo that launched in 2021, there is an &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.instagram.com/themodernhouse/?hl=en&quot;>;Instagram feed&lt;/a>; with more than 750,000 followers (“Best interiors Instagram account” – Vogue), several coffee table books, a £15-an-issue glossy magazine, a podcast called Homing In, a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/@themodernhouse_films&quot;>;YouTube channel&lt;/a>;, and an online directory of architects, designers and other brands endorsed by the firm.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Its headquarters is in a former ecclesiastical building in south London, but it also differs from many other estate agencies in not having a traditional high street branch network. It says that “we try not to define ourselves by a high street presence in a particular location”. However, it is signed up to the leading property portals such as Rightmove and Zoopla.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The 300-plus properties listed for sale at the time of writing included a £9m penthouse near London&#39;s Hyde Park, a £7.5m five-bedroom house in Surrey, and a striking detached property in Brighton with a £3.2m price tag.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;4a42448037efbe7fd9807825898f52f8bfdd9407&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/4a42448037efbe7fd9807825898f52f8bfdd9407/0_249_4835_2902/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;St Lawrence, Isle of Wight&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;This former second world war bunker in St Lawrence, Isle of Wight, was for sale through The Modern House for £2.25m.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: The Modern House&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;The Modern House grew quickly during the pandemic, when millions of people stuck at home in lockdowns became hooked on browsing property websites as they plotted – or simply fantasised about – a new life, perhaps in the countryside, in a market town or on the coast.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;According to Companies House filings, The Modern House had 26 employees in 2019, shortly before Covid struck. By early 2022 this had climbed to 59, and it is thought the number of employees hit between 75 and 80 this year.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A recent post on Glassdoor – a website where people post anonymous reviews of their current or former employers – claimed leadership changes at the firm this year had “completely turned [the] company upside down,” and added that a shake-up “has resulted in a massive redundancy and lots of people leaving the company”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The housing market has slowed in recent months as the Bank of England has raised interest rates sharply, with affordability constraints leaving many would-be buyers sitting on the sidelines. The Bank had raised interest rates at 14 consecutive rate-setting meetings up until September as it tried to tame inflation. On Thursday, it chose to keep the base rate on hold for a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/nov/02/bank-of-england-leaves-interest-rates-unchanged-inflation-slowdown?CMP=share_btn_tw&quot;>;second time in a row at 5.25%&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Last month, the Halifax said UK house prices &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/oct/06/buyers-market-fuels-fastest-fall-in-house-prices-in-14-years&quot;>;fell at their fastest annual rate in 14 years&lt;/a>; in September, while its rival lender Nationwide said &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/oct/02/uk-house-prices-drop-53-with-falls-in-every-region-says-nationwide&quot;>;property values fell by 5.3%&lt;/a>; in the year to September, with drops in price in every region of the country. However, Nationwide &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/nov/01/uk-house-prices-rose-unexpectedly-in-october-index-shows&quot;>;said on Wednesday&lt;/a>; that UK house prices rose unexpectedly by 0.9% month on month in October, although they were still down 3.3% year on year.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;555c09d45f361b2426384b7256462444001eff10&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/555c09d45f361b2426384b7256462444001eff10/190_0_5282_3169/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;The Chestertons estate agents in Little Venice, London&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;One of the UK&#39;s oldest estate agents, Chestertons, was sold a fortnight ago as other firms reduce their staff.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Andy Hall/The Observer&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;The Modern House – which declined multiple requests to speak to the Guardian – is not the only estate agent taking action in response to the slowdown. The property trade press recently reported that Knight Frank had &lt;a href=&quot;https://propertyindustryeye.com/knight-frank-plans-mass-job-cuts-amid-downturn-in-uk-housing-market/&quot;>;initiated a redundancy consultation process with staff&lt;/a>; and had indicated that up to 3% of roles were at risk.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A fortnight ago, it emerged that one of the UK&#39;s oldest estate agents, Chestertons, had been sold to a subsidiary of European real estate services and technology group Emeria &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ft.com/content/067206be-0e43-40cb-9712-fb7758355950&quot;>;for a reported £100m&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Earlier this year, shareholders in the online estate agent Purplebricks voted overwhelmingly &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/jun/02/purplebricks-one-pound-sale-to-rival-strike-backed-by-shareholders&quot;>;to sell the company for only £1&lt;/a>; to Strike, a competitor backed by the telecoms tycoon Sir &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/business/charles-dunstone&quot;>;Charles Dunstone&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 16:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia-Ukraine war live: Russian forces intent on capturing Avdiivka coking plant, says mayor]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/nov/04/russia-ukraine-war-latest-news-putin-zelenskiy]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T08:14:44Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/9a75dce770ecaa170b9d92d4394f909a7e5c8810/0_0_8640_5760/master/8640.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=926295a80756c863856e4cb8f560a42d&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Ukrainian forces continue to fight to retake Bakhmut, which was captured by Russian forces in May, following a year long battle in Russia&#39;s war on Ukraine.&lt;/div>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 16:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[White House denounces Fox News over host’s ‘foul’ remarks on CNN pair]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/media/2023/nov/03/white-house-biden-condemns-fox-news-mark-levin-cnn-israel-hamas]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-03T20:54:34Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/6f40ca9b067b2d81986a18d9be64e47ecf8abad6/0_0_4477_2689/master/4477.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=c8b1a2d26372eec72d86a5bea656edfd&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;CNN called Mark Levin&#39;s comments &#39;wildly uninformed, inappropriate and shameful&#39;.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;For the second time in two days, the White House denounced Fox News over remarks by a host relating to the Israel-Hamas war, following &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/media/2023/nov/02/fox-news-jesse-watters-arab-americans-white-house&quot;>;condemnation&lt;/a>; of Jesse Watters&#39; apparent incitement of violence against Arab Americans with condemnation of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.foxnews.com/shows/life-liberty-levin&quot;>;Mark Levin&lt;/a>; for &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mediamatters.org/mark-levin/fox-host-mark-levin-falsely-says-cnn-anchor-wolf-blitzers-parents-werent-victims-one-way&quot;>;calling&lt;/a>; two CNN anchors “self-hating Jews”.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/media/2023/nov/02/fox-news-jesse-watters-arab-americans-white-house&quot;>;White House condemns Fox News over &#39;sickening attack&#39; on Arab Americans&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Andrew Bates, a spokesperson, said: “President Biden believes in an America where we come together against hate and don&#39;t fan its flames. But not only is Fox News aligning with those who fan the flames of hate – Fox is paying their salaries.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Levin, who hosts &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.foxnews.com/video/shows/life-liberty-levin&quot;>;Life, Liberty &amp;amp; Levin&lt;/a>;, a Fox News weekend show, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mediaite.com/news/fox-news-host-says-cnn-anchors-like-jake-tapper-are-self-hating-jews-and-falsely-claims-wolf-blitzers-parents-were-not-holocaust-victims/&quot;>;attacked&lt;/a>; Wolf Blitzer and Jake Tapper of CNN on The Mark Levin Show, his daily &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.westwoodone.com/programs/news-and-talk/daily-talk/the-mark-levin-show/&quot;>;radio show&lt;/a>; which is syndicated by Westwood One.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Though Levin, who is Jewish, acknowledged Blitzer&#39;s family history – all the CNN anchor&#39;s grandparents were killed in the Holocaust – Levin said Blitzer&#39;s parents “weren&#39;t victims”. Regarding Blitzer&#39;s coverage of the Israel-Hamas war, Levin called the host “a dumb bastard” with “a hearing problem and an IQ problem” who “wants Israel to die”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Blitzer was a “self-hating Jew”, Levin said, reaching for a label he previously applied to Tapper.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;CNN &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mediaite.com/media/cnn-hammers-mark-levin-for-antisemitic-and-shameful-comments-about-its-anchors/&quot;>;called&lt;/a>; Levin&#39;s comments “wildly uninformed, inappropriate and shameful”, adding that his “antisemitic rhetoric is dangerous, offensive and should be universally denounced”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;On Friday, the White House did so.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Lying to insult the pain that families suffered in the Holocaust has absolutely no place in America,” Bates said. “None. Sadly, this is not the first time in recent months that a Fox News host made sickening remarks about the Holocaust.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Despite &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nbcnews.com/news/auschwitz-memorial-criticizes-fox-news-greg-gutfeld-saying-jews-surviv-rcna96200&quot;>;condemnation&lt;/a>; from the Auschwitz Memorial, Fox has not even disagreed with Greg Gutfeld&#39;s reprehensible &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nbcnews.com/news/auschwitz-memorial-criticizes-fox-news-greg-gutfeld-saying-jews-surviv-rcna96200&quot;>;claim&lt;/a>; that Nazi labour camps taught Jews to be &#39;useful&#39;.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In July, during a debate over the rightwing claim that some Black people benefited from being enslaved, Gutfeld said on air: “Did you ever [read] Man&#39;s Search for Meaning? Vik[tor] Frankl talks about how you had to survive in a concentration camp by having skills. You had to be useful. Utility. Utility kept you alive.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;On Friday, in his statement on Levin&#39;s comments, Bates said: “It isn&#39;t even the first time this week that a Fox host chose to abuse their platform and spread hate.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A day before, Bates condemned comments in which Watters, discussing instances of pictures of Israeli hostages held by Hamas being taken down from public display, seemed to advocate violence.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Watters said: “If you&#39;re an Arab American in this country, and you rip down posters of Jewish hostages, American hostages, no.不不不。 Someone is going to get punched in the face.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Referring to a recent killing in Illinois, now the subject of murder and hate crime charges, Bates said: “Even after the heartbreaking killing of a six-year-old Palestinian American child and a surge in violence against Muslims and Arab Americans, two nights ago Jesse Watters made vile comments that attack the dignity of all Americans, saying he&#39;s &#39;done&#39; with Arab Americans and Muslims.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“And Fox News continues to promote the cynical, dangerous lie that fighting against Islamophobia is somehow at odds with fighting antisemitism, even as they permit hosts to hurt their viewers with foul antisemitic comments.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“President Biden will always stand up against antisemitism, Islamophobia, and all forms of hate. Fox News needs to stop standing up on behalf of hate.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Fox News did not immediately respond to a request for comment.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 15:22:01 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>